    <section>
        <h2>Problem Statement</h2>
        <p>The tourism industry is dynamic and demands deep data analysis for effective decision-making. Over-tourism poses challenges such as infrastructure strain and environmental impact. This project applies descriptive and diagnostic analysis to address these issues.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Abstract</h2>
        <p>This project explores structured tourism data from Kaggle (2014–2020) using Python and tools like Pandas, Matplotlib, and Scikit-learn. It aims to identify trends, forecast demand, and suggest business strategies. Insights support sustainable tourism and strategic decisions.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>System Requirements</h2>
        <h3>Hardware</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Intel i5+ or AMD Ryzen</li>
            <li>8 GB RAM (16 GB recommended)</li>
            <li>10 GB free space</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Software</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Python 3.8+</li>
            <li>Google Colab / Jupyter Notebook</li>
            <li>Libraries: pandas, numpy, matplotlib, seaborn, scikit-learn, streamlit, flask, gradio, fastapi</li>
            <li>Version Control: Git & GitHub</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Project Objectives</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Analyze tourism trends and seasonal patterns</li>
            <li>Forecast visitor numbers</li>
            <li>Segment customers and understand preferences</li>
            <li>Support business decision-making</li>
            <li>Enhance planning and promote sustainable tourism</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Project Workflow</h2>
        <p>Data Acquisition → Data Cleaning → EDA → Feature Engineering → Modeling → Assessment → Visualization → Deployment</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Dataset Description</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Source: Kaggle</li>
            <li>Years: 2014–2020</li>
            <li>Structured CSV with fields: Year, Country, Arrivals, Departures, Region, Indicators</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Data Preprocessing</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Handled missing values using imputation</li>
            <li>Removed duplicates</li>
            <li>Standardized country/column names</li>
            <li>Formatted data types</li>
            <li>Detected and treated outliers</li>
            <li>Created features like growth rate and COVID impact flags</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Descriptive statistics on tourist data</li>
            <li>Distribution and trend analysis using visualizations</li>
            <li>Regional comparisons and COVID-19 impact studies</li>
            <li>Correlation analysis and insights via charts and maps</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Insights & Interpretation</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Countries with high tourism saw sharp drops in 2020</li>
            <li>Europe remains dominant in global tourism inflow</li>
            <li>COVID-19 caused a significant decline in all travel</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Recommendations</h2>
        <h3>Short-Term Actions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Promote less-crowded destinations</li>
            <li>Use dashboards for real-time decision support</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Long-Term Strategic Moves</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Integrate marketing automation tools</li>
            <li>Enhance data pipelines and dashboards</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Visualizations / Dashboard</h2>
        <p>Include visuals like line plots, heatmaps, and dashboards from Tableau or Plotly with descriptions of each.</p>
    </section>

